<a name="installation"></a>
## Installation

<a name="server-requirements"></a>
### Server Requirements

The Vault project is build on top of codeigniter. It has a few system requirements. You can use codeigniter Homestead (virtual machine) as your local codeigniter development environment.

However, if you are not using Homestead, you will need to make sure your server meets the following requirements:


- Apache or Nginx
- PHP >= 5.6.4(Use latest php version)
- OpenSSL PHP Extension
- PDO PHP Extension
- Mbstring PHP Extension
- MySQL > 3.0. or mariadb(Use latest mysql/mariadb version)


<a name="installing-Vault"></a>

#### Installing Vault 


###### via GitLab
1. The project is in Gitlab Environment. gitlab repository is ```https://gitlab.com/swatich123/vault-project.git```.
2. before setting project through gitlab make sure that you are set as a developer in Gitlab. If not, ask Gitlab Administrator to give you developer role.
3. Clone the repository via ```Git clone https://gitlab.com/swatich123/vault-project.git```. Default branch is ``master``, make sure in ``master`` branch.
3. Change the config file base url path is:  application/config/config.php.
4. Create a database.
5. Change the database credentials in:  application/config/database.php.
6. You application is ready.

###### via Zip Download
1. Unzip the package.
2. Change the config file base url path is:  application/config/config.php.
3. Create a database.
4. Change the database credentials in:  application/config/database.php.


###### Development Server

 If you have PHP installed locally and you would like to use PHP's built-in development server to serve your application, you may use to start a development server at `http://localhost/project-name`:

 

